# Kids App AI Guidelines

- Keep changes beginner-friendly and avoid over-engineering.
- Preserve current gameplay behavior unless explicitly asked to change it.
- Prefer small, incremental edits over broad rewrites.
- Keep files modular by concern (`config`, `state`, `audio`, `questions`, `dom`, `app`).
- The shipped entry is `app.runtime.js` so the app runs from `file://`. ES modules (`import`/`export`) only work over `http://` or `https://` unless you add a bundler.
- Maintain accessibility features (keyboard support, `aria-*`, focus visibility, reduced motion).
- Use safe browser APIs (guard `localStorage`, audio play failures).
- Avoid adding heavy dependencies unless requested.
- Keep copy text kid-friendly and encouraging.
- When changing UI, ensure mobile-first layout still works.
- After meaningful edits, run lints and fix introduced issues.
